The storage module doesn't declare `core` module dependency, like this
```
    @Override public String[] requiredModules() {
        return new String[] {CoreModule.NAME};
    }
```

So, in some cases, storage module may(based on JVM, OS, etc.) start before core. As a result, storage module can't find any model, which is based on core class scan in `start` phase.

`source.workload.namespace` should be used to assemble the service name, by following rule `source.workload.namespace`.`source.workload.name`.

The ref doc is https://istio.io/docs/reference/config/policy-and-telemetry/attribute-vocabulary/

